---
description: n8n-decanter repo — how to treat decanted workflow files
alwaysApply: true
---

This repository is managed by **n8n-decanter**. The authoritative contract is
`AGENTS.md` at the repo root — read it in full before editing workflow files.

Hard rules (violating any of these corrupts sync state):

- `jsCode` in any `workflow.json` is only a `//@file:code/<name>` placeholder. Never
  inline code there — edit the referenced source file in the folder's `code/` subdir.
- `workflow.json` is a read-only structure snapshot — structure changes happen in n8n
  (editor or MCP tools), never by editing the file. The one meaningful local edit is
  re-pointing a `//@file:` placeholder.
- Code-node source is authored as files here and synced by decanter — never edit a
  node's `jsCode` on the instance (UI or MCP tools).
- Never edit `.decanter.json` or `.decanter-auth.json` (machine state / credentials).
- Never write a `// @ts-n8n sha256:` line — the tool appends it on push.
- Code nodes run as a function body with a top-level `return`, no `import`/`require`
  in `.js` nodes.
- Run `npm run typecheck` after editing node source. `push` writes the DRAFT and only
  when asked; `publish` is the deliberate go-live step; never `--force` without an
  explicit instruction.

Cursor applies this as guidance only; the n8n-decanter CLI enforces the same invariants
at `push` regardless of which tool made the edit.
